Citations
Date:  0/0/1927
Source:  Sheep & Wool Industry
Author:  SMITH
Vol / Page:  73
Edition:
Quote:  Prior to the commencement of shearing the board is fitted with `tar-pots', so called because in the early days tar was used to put on the cuts accidentally made by the shearers; but as tar [74] would not scour out ..., it is now usual to use an antiseptic liquid.
